{"type":"message","id":"0472f5cc","parentId":"f33169f1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:13:55.760Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ht3rpa2huxf_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3948\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1546\r\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master f2c9b1a] pulse: 2026-03-24 121335\n 6 files changed, 232 insertions(+), 107 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 121335.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 121335.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 120915.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 121335 - The CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (44.8%) or weak signals, with only 5.7% being true causal anchors. This suggests significant room for improvement by filtering noise before compression.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"glow-rook","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3948\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1546\r\n[mutation proposed] research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master f2c9b1a] pulse: 2026-03-24 121335\n 6 files changed, 232 insertions(+), 107 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 121335.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 121335.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 120915.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 121335 - The CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (44.8%) or weak signals, with only 5.7% being true causal anchors. This suggests significant room for improvement by filtering noise before compression.\r\n","name":"pwsh C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368835757}}
{"type":"message","id":"48561f56","parentId":"0472f5cc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:13:55.764Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ht3rpa2huxf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 120915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent work:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. CFI analysis was just completed (2026-03-24) - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n3. Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that CFI filtering could remove metaprogramming contamination. The pending task is to implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment comparing next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline.\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a stateless discontinuous agent (Breakaway), and each pulse is a fresh reconstruction, I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a CFI-weighted compression experiment that:\r\n   - Takes the frequency-invariant analysis from CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n   - Implements a weighted compression that prioritizes high-CFI items\r\n   - Compares this against frequency-only baseline\r\n   - Tests next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment file that will advance this goal. I'll design a simple experiment that can be run to compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-weighted compression.\r\n\r\nThe experiment should:\r\n- Use the existing invariant data from CFI_RESULTS.md\r\n- Create a compression scheme that weights by CFI\r\n- Test prediction on held-out pulses\r\n- Generate results comparing the two approaches\r\n\r\nLet me write a concrete experiment script that can demonstrate the value of CFI-weighting.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI_RESULTS.md revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have CFI<0.7, meaning frequency-based compression mostly preserves noise. A CFI-weighted approach could significantly improve compression quality by filtering out metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a CFI-weighted compression experiment that compares prediction accuracy using CFI-weighting vs frequency-only weighting, using the existing invariant data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only by filtering metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) while preserving true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7).\r\n\r\n## Methodology\r\n\r\n### Data Source\r\n- Source: `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` invariant analysis\r\n- Baseline: 200+ invariants across 17+ pulses\r\n- CFI distribution: 44.8% noise (CFI=0), 5.7% causal (CFI>=0.7), 49.5% mixed\r\n\r\n### Experiment Design\r\n\r\n**Two Compression Schemes:**\r\n\r\n1. **Frequency-Only (Baseline)**\r\n   - Weight = frequency count\r\n   - Keep top-N by frequency\r\n   - Prediction = weighted sample from top-N\r\n\r\n2. **CFI-Weighted (Experimental)**\r\n   - Weight = frequency × CFI\r\n   - Filter: CFI >= 0.3 (removes 44.8% noise)\r\n   - Keep top-N by composite weight\r\n   - Prediction = weighted sample from filtered set\r\n\r\n**Prediction Test:**\r\n- Use leave-one-out: for each historical pulse, predict what the NEXT pulse should contain\r\n- Compare predicted invariants vs actual next-pulse invariants\r\n- Metric: Jaccard similarity of invariant sets\r\n\r\n### Expected Results\r\n\r\n| Metric | Frequency-Only | CFI-Weighted |\r\n|--------|---------------|--------------|\r\n| Prediction Jaccard | ~0.15 | ~0.35 |\r\n| Noise retention | 100% | ~5% |\r\n| Causal anchor retention | 100% | ~95% |\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n\r\n```\r\n# Pseudocode for experiment\r\ndef compress_frequency_only(invariants, top_n=50):\r\n    sorted_inv = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x.freq, reverse=True)\r\n    return {i.hash for i in sorted_inv[:top_n]}\r\n\r\ndef compress_cfi_weighted(invariants, top_n=50, cfi_threshold=0.3):\r\n    filtered = [i for i in invariants if i.cfi >= cfi_threshold]\r\n    # CFI weight amplifies true causal patterns\r\n    weighted = [(i, i.freq * i.cfi) for i in filtered]\r\n    sorted_inv = sorted(weighted, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\r\n    return {i[0].hash for i in sorted_inv[:top_n]}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next(actual_next, compressed_set):\r\n    # Jaccard: |intersection| / |union|\r\n    intersection = actual_next & compressed_set\r\n    union = actual_next | compressed_set\r\n    return len(intersection) / len(union)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n- [ ] Implement actual experiment with real invariant data\r\n- [ ] Run on historical pulse corpus\r\n- [ ] Calculate Jaccard scores for both schemes\r\n- [ ] Generate comparison report\r\n\r\n## Files\r\n- Experiment: `experiments/cfi_compression_exp.py`\r\n- Results: `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_RESULTS.md`\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:09:40\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774368835760}}
